html: FY19 Q3 ends with Netflix having raised their revenue by 30% YOY to $5B. Stock increased as a result of the report 10 days ago. Took on debt in range of $2B to acquire more IP to combat Disney+, and spent $15B on content this yr. Debt as a cause of content isn't a bad thing lol.
